OL,3,CCouncils warn SEND deficits mean they
OL,4,Ccould go bankrupt 'overnight'
OL,6,FThe data - from the County Councils
OL,7,FNetwork (CCN), Society of County
OL,8,FTreasurers and Association of Local
OL,9,FAuthority Treasurers - suggests the
OL,10,Ffigure will balloon to #5.9 billion
OL,11,Fnext year, and then #8 bn after that.
OL,13,FLarge and often rural councils
OL,14,Frepresented by the CCN have the
OL,15,Flargest deficits. This year #2 billion
OL,16,F- or half of the total deficit - falls
OL,17,Fon the shoulders of its 38 members who
OL,18,Fsay the situation is now
OL,19,F"unmanageable". Their deficits are
OL,20,Fexpected to rise to #2.7 billion in
OL,21,F2025/26, and then #3.8 billion.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
