OL,3,CCouncils warn SEND deficits mean they
OL,4,Ccould go bankrupt 'overnight'
OL,6,FThe councils have only been able to
OL,7,Fcarry the deficits because the
OL,8,Fgovernment introduced an accounting
OL,9,Fmethod known as a 'statutory override'
OL,10,Fthat keeps the money off the books,
OL,11,Fbut it is due to expire in March 2026.
OL,13,FA separate survey of its members by
OL,14,Fthe CCN reveals that 26 councils
OL,15,Fbelieve they will have to trigger a
OL,16,Fsection 114 and effectively declare
OL,17,Fbankruptcy by the end of 2027 if the
OL,18,Ffunding crisis is not fixed. Wiltshire
OL,19,FCouncil is one of 18 councils warning
OL,20,Fit would go insolvent immediately if
OL,21,Fthe override is withdrawn.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
