OL,3,CCouncils warn SEND deficits mean they
OL,4,Ccould go bankrupt 'overnight'
OL,6,FCouncillor Kate Foale, the SEND CCN
OL,7,Fspokeswoman, said: "With the clock
OL,8,Fticking to March 2026 when these
OL,9,Fdeficits are placed back onto
OL,10,Fcouncils' budget books, the government
OL,11,Fmust provide immediate clarity on a
OL,12,Fnational solution to eliminating or
OL,13,Fmanaging councils' deficits. But this
OL,14,Fis only one part of the solution. We
OL,15,Falso need root and branch reform of
OL,16,Fthe SEND system to address the key
OL,17,Fissues driving demand and cost,
OL,18,Fincluding flipping the system to make
OL,19,Fmainstream schools more inclusive for
OL,20,FSEND pupils."
